---
import Base from '../../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Callout from '../../../../components/Callout.astro';
import AdSlot from '../../../../components/AdSlot.astro';
import Mastery from '../../../../components/Mastery.astro';
import TrustRow from '../../../../components/TrustRow.astro';
import { attempt } from '../../../../data/site.js';
---

<Base title="Retirement of a partner — Advanced Accounting Ch 4" active="papers">
  <main class="page" style="max-width: 1024px;">
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 48px; justify-content: center; align-items: flex-start;">
      <article style="max-width: 640px; min-width: 0; flex: 1;">
        <Breadcrumb crumbs={[
          { label: 'CA Intermediate', href: '/intermediate/' },
          { label: 'Paper 1 · Adv. Accounting', href: '/intermediate/advanced-accounting/' },
          { label: 'Ch 4 · Partnership', href: '/intermediate/advanced-accounting/' },
          { label: 'Retirement of a partner' },
        ]} />

        <h1 style="margin: 0; font-size: 30px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.25;">Retirement of a partner</h1>
        <div style="margin: 12px 0 8px;">
          <TrustRow attempt={attempt.name} updated="30 Jun 2026" source="ICAI SM Mod 2, Unit 4; Partnership Act s.37" />
        </div>
        <div style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-3); margin-bottom: 24px;">About 10 min read · 1 worked example</div>

        <div class="article">
          <p>
            Retirement mirrors admission. The same three settlements appear — ratio, goodwill,
            revaluation — but the direction reverses: continuing partners <strong>gain</strong> share and
            must <strong>compensate</strong> the outgoing partner. One new question appears: how is the
            retiring partner actually paid out?
          </p>

          <h2 id="s1">1. Gaining ratio</h2>
          <p>The gaining ratio is the ratio in which continuing partners acquire the outgoing partner's share:</p>
          <div class="formula">Gaining ratio = New ratio − Old ratio</div>
          <p>
            If the question gives no new ratio, the continuing partners are assumed to gain in their
            <strong>old inter-se ratio</strong> — so the old ratio simply drops the retiring partner.
          </p>

          <Callout kind="example" label="Worked example 1">
            <p>A, B and C share profits 3:2:1. B retires; A and C agree to share 3:1 in future. The firm's goodwill is valued at ₹1,20,000. Who pays B for goodwill, and how much?</p>
            <div class="working-note">
              <div class="working-note-label">Working note 1 — gaining ratio</div>
              A: 3/4 − 3/6 = 9/12 − 6/12 = <strong>3/12</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp; C: 1/4 − 1/6 = 3/12 − 2/12 = <strong>1/12</strong><br />
              Gaining ratio A:C = <strong>3 : 1</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="working-note" style="margin-top: 10px;">
              <div class="working-note-label">Working note 2 — goodwill adjustment</div>
              B's share of goodwill = 2/6 × 1,20,000 = <strong>₹40,000</strong><br />
              A bears 40,000 × 3/4 = <strong>₹30,000</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp; C bears 40,000 × 1/4 = <strong>₹10,000</strong><br />
              Entry: A's Capital Dr 30,000 · C's Capital Dr 10,000 · To B's Capital 40,000
            </div>
          </Callout>

          <Callout kind="mistake">
            <p>
              Debiting the continuing partners in the <em>old</em> or <em>new</em> ratio. Goodwill
              compensation always follows the <strong>gaining ratio</strong> — whoever gains share pays
              for it, exactly as the sacrificing ratio governs admission.
            </p>
          </Callout>

          <h2 id="s2">2. Revaluation and reserves</h2>
          <p>
            Revaluation profit or loss, and accumulated reserves/losses, belong to <strong>all partners
            including the retiring one, in the old ratio</strong> — they arose during everyone's tenure.
            Do this before computing the final amount due.
          </p>
        </div>

        <AdSlot />

        <div class="article">
          <h2 id="s3" style="margin-top: 0;">3. Settling the amount due</h2>
          <p>
            The balance on the retiring partner's capital account (after goodwill, revaluation and
            reserves) is paid as the deed provides: lump sum, instalments, or transfer to a
            <strong>loan account</strong>.
          </p>

          <Callout kind="pointer" label="Exam pointer · Section 37">
            <p>
              If the amount stays unpaid and the deed is silent, Section 37 of the Indian Partnership
              Act 1932 gives the outgoing partner a choice: <strong>interest at 6% p.a.</strong> on the
              unpaid balance, or the <strong>share of profits</strong> attributable to the use of his money.
              This is a recurring MCQ — remember both branches, and that it's the <em>outgoing partner's</em> option.
            </p>
          </Callout>

          <Callout kind="amendment" label={`Verified for ${attempt.name}`}>
            <p>
              No amendments affect this topic for the {attempt.name} attempt. Death of a partner follows
              the same framework, plus the executor's entitlement to profits up to the date of death
              (usually via time-basis or turnover-basis estimation).
            </p>
          </Callout>
        </div>

        <div style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; padding-top: 20px;">
          <a href="/practice/quiz/?topic=retirement" class="btn btn-primary">Practice this topic</a>
          <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; margin-top: 24px; gap: 16px;">
            <a href="/intermediate/advanced-accounting/partnership-accounts/admission-of-a-partner/" class="card card-e1" style="flex: 1; padding: 14px 16px; text-decoration: none; color: var(--text);">
              <span style="display: block; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); margin-bottom: 2px;">← Previous</span>
              <span style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600;">Admission of a partner</span>
            </a>
            <span style="flex: 1;"></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <aside style="width: 240px; flex-shrink: 0; position: sticky; top: 24px;" class="notes-sidebar">
        <div class="overline" style="font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 10px;">On this page</div>
        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; border-left: 2px solid var(--border);">
          <a href="#s1" style="padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text); font-weight: 650; text-decoration: none; border-left: 2px solid var(--accent); margin-left: -2px;">1. Gaining ratio</a>
          <a href="#s2" style="padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); text-decoration: none;">2. Revaluation &amp; reserves</a>
          <a href="#s3" style="padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); text-decoration: none;">3. Settlement (s.37)</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 16px;">
          <div style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 650; margin-bottom: 8px;">Your standing</div>
          <Mastery level={0} topicId="p1-ch4-retirement" />
          <div style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-3); margin-top: 8px; line-height: 1.5;">
            Practising moves this up. No penalty for reading slowly.
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .notes-sidebar { display: none; }
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    import { getMastery } from '../../../../scripts/store.js';
    const labels = ['Not started', 'Familiar', 'Proficient', 'Mastered ✓'];
    const el = document.querySelector('[data-mastery="p1-ch4-retirement"]');
    if (el) {
      const level = getMastery('p1-ch4-retirement');
      el.querySelectorAll('.seg').forEach((seg, i) => seg.classList.toggle('on', i < level));
      const label = el.querySelector('[data-mastery-label]');
      if (label) label.textContent = labels[level];
    }
  </script>
</Base>
